QA of processed data by the new telog_dl function

Source data

Telog data between 07/01/2015 and 10/01/2016 were extracted using the original method and new method.

The data generated by Telog_dl_multiple_program_20161121.r (original) are:

  • telog_dl_multiple_output_15min_averaged_1min.csv
  • telog_dl_multiple_output_15min_averaged_2.5min.csv

The data generated by Telog_dl_multiple_program_20170118a.R (new) is:

  • telog_dl_multiple_output_20170119_a.csv

Rows check: pass

The original data contains 43969 rows, which matches the new data that also has 43969 rows.

Columns check: pass

The original data contains 443 columns, while the new one contains 446 columns.

The following columns are present in the original data but not the new one:

DATE_TIME
C_16_SWO_LEVEL_2298
C_16_TRUNK_LEVEL_2295
I_UDLLFCS_SYPHON_LEVEL_5391
I_UDLLH04_INTERCEPTOR_LEVEL_1816
I_USESH11_INTERCEPTOR_LEVEL_6500
I_WLLH11_INTERCEPTOR_LEVEL_6624

The following columns are present in the new data but not the original one:

dtime
C_29_TRUNK_LEVEL
D_02_TRUNK_LEVEL
D_02_SWO_LEVEL
D_02_DWO_LEVEL
I_UDLLFCS_SYPHON_LEVEL_NORTH
I_UDLLPPCS_INTERCEPTOR_LEVEL_SOUTH
I_USE285H11_INTERCEPTOR_LEVEL
I_WLL10H11_INTERCEPTOR_LEVEL
R_20_INTERCEPTOR_RADAR_LEVEL

Among those descrapancies:

  1. C_16 : the measurement had ended on 6/11/2012, and was omitted in new data;
  2. I_UDLLFCS: the measurement name has been changed to SYPHON_LEVEL_NORTH;
  3. I_UDLLH04: the site name has been changed to I_UDLLPPCS;
  4. I_USEH11: the site name has been changed to I_USE285H11;
  5. I_WLLH11: the site name has been changed to I_WLL10H11;
  6. C_29, D_02, R_20: the measurements were included in the site list, but was not downloaded somehow in the original data.

Value check: pass

Each value in the new and original dataset were compared, data that shows a discrapancy of larger than +/-0.01 are listed below:



To find out why these discrapancy happened, a random row from the above table is selected (re-run this code chunk will produce different results):

DATE_TIME old_avg new_avg delta site
2016-03-22 09:15:00 6.184713 7.421656 -1.236943 D_70_TRUNK_LEVEL_1691

Then, the raw data within the time range (-5min to +20min) are extracted from Telog server:

trend_data_time trend_data_avg
2016-03-22 09:17:30 7.473556
2016-03-22 09:20:00 7.473556
2016-03-22 09:22:30 7.421656
2016-03-22 09:25:00 7.369756
2016-03-22 09:27:30 7.369756
2016-03-22 09:30:00 7.369756
2016-03-22 09:32:30 7.317856
2016-03-22 09:35:00 7.317856

As seen, the discrapancy is caused by the original script that accidentally treats missing value as zero rather than NA, and lowers the mean when data are aggregated. The new script processes missing values properly.
